about.summary: A system for 'declaratively' creating graphics, based on "The Grammar of Graphics". You provide the data, tell 'ggplot2' how to map variables to aesthetics, what graphical primitives to use, and it takes care of the details.

name: r-ggplot2
raw_recipe:
{% set version = '3.1.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggplot2
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggplot2_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggplot2/ggplot2_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: bfde297f3b4732e7f560078f4ce131812a70877e6b5b1d41a772c394939e0c79

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-digest
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-lazyeval
    - r-mgcv
    - r-plyr >=1.7.1
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rlang >=0.2.1
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble
    - r-viridislite
    - r-withr >=2.0.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-mass
    - r-digest
    - r-gtable >=0.1.1
    - r-lazyeval
    - r-mgcv
    - r-plyr >=1.7.1
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rlang >=0.2.1
    - r-scales >=0.5.0
    - r-tibble
    - r-viridislite
    - r-withr >=2.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggplot2')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggplot2')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://ggplot2.tidyverse.org, https://github.com/tidyverse/ggplot2
  license: GPL-2
  summary: A system for 'declaratively' creating graphics, based on "The Grammar of Graphics".
    You provide the data, tell 'ggplot2' how to map variables to aesthetics, what graphical
    primitives to use, and it takes care of the details.
  license_family: GPL2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ocefpaf
